<TITLE> Padma bridge construction by Sept: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Communications minister Syed Abul Hossain anounced the government's goal to start construction of the bridge over the river Padma by September. Answering to a question by AKM Mustafizur Rahman in parliament on Monday, he said, "There are plans to start construction of the Padma bridge by September of 1010 and finish it by December of 2013." The minister informed the MPs that primary work of the bridge has already started, as part of which the planning maps have already been finalised. Compensations are being paid to the affected for land acquisition. The pre-qualification documents for employing contractors have also been formulated, Hossain said. The parliament resumed after a six-day break at 3pm with speaker Abdul Hamid in the chair . Answering to another question by Matiur Rahman, the communications minister said, "All highways of the country would gradually be upgraded to four lanes." Responding to yet another question, the minister said the work of broadening the Chittagong highway to four lanes would start soon. b
